<assessment id="u4_m3_cq2_tutor3">
    <title>Tutor</title>
    <page>
    <question id="q1">
        <body>A publishing company wanted to test whether
                <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133435-0500" content="the "?>typing
                speeds differ when using word processor A or word processor B. The typing speeds (in
                words per minute) are recorded for a random sample of 25
                <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133446-0500"?>typists<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133444-0500" content="secretaries"?>
                using processor A, and for another (different) random sample of 25
                <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133457-0500"?>typists<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133455-0500" content="secretaries"?>
                using word processor
                B.<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133501-0500"?> Which "case"
                does this study fall into?<?oxy_insert_end?></body>
        <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
            <choice value="A">Comparing two
                    means<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133534-0500"?>&#8212;<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133531-0500" content=" - "?>independent
                    samples</choice>
            <choice value="B">Comparing two
                    means<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133537-0500"?>&#8212;<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133535-0500" content=" - "?>matched
                    pairs</choice>
            <choice value="C">Comparing more than two
                    means<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133543-0500"?>&#8212;<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133541-0500" content=" - "?>independent
                    sample<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133544-0500"?>s<?oxy_insert_end?></choice>
        </multiple_choice>
        <part>
            <response match="A" score="10">
                <feedback>Correct. Indeed, this example calls for comparing two means (the mean
                        typing speeds
                        <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133700-0500"?>using<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133659-0500" content="of"?>
                        the two word processors), and since each of the two samples was chosen
                        randomly, they are independent.</feedback>
            </response>
            <response match="B">
                <feedback>Incorrect. While it is true that this example calls for
                        comparing two means (the mean typing speeds
                        <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133710-0500"?>using<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101128T133709-0500" content="of"?>
                        the two word processors), note that each of the samples was chosen
                        randomly.</feedback>
            </response>
            <response match="C">
                <feedback>Incorrect. While it is true that the samples here are
                    independent (since each was chosen randomly), note that in this example, we are
                    comparing only two word processors.</feedback>
            </response>
        </part>
    </question></page>
</assessment>
